review_blob: Pours a beautiful clear amber beer. Head disappears quickly. Not a lot of aroma. A hint of hops and somewhat grassy. Tastes sweet at first, then malty and finally a subtle bitterness. A clean and refreshing ale. A great alternative to a lager.

A cloudy golden beer with a firm head. Yeasty aroma. Taste starts rather sweet and yeasty, and evolves to a bitter ending and a long lasting aftertaste. Be careful with this one, its a quite alcoholic beer. Apparantly, this beer is the same as the better known Kapittel Abt.

Hazy colour, almost amber. Head diminishes quickly. Aroma of banana, vanilla, yeast and some smokiness. The smokiness is even more represented in the taste. Ends in a soft and rather dry bitterness. A well balanced beer with an original twist (the smokiness).

Coffee-like colour. Head disapears immediately, only a small head stays. Aroma: banana, chocolate, bread, brown sugar. Taste is more bitter than one would expect after smelling the beer. What a full and rich flavor. Hints of coffee, chocolate, malts, and quite a dry finish. This beer has a stout-ish taste and smell, but is definitely more complex. Its high alcohol percentage is barely noticable. A beer you should have tried!

Not a typical christmas beer. Hazy color with a small head. Smells spicy and malty. Taste is somewhat between a saison dottignies and the guldenberg from De Ranke. Hoppy, malty, lemon zest, a little bit of sweetness, clear bitterness and dryness at the end.
Clear golden beer with a small head. Not a lot of aroma. A little bit of fruitiness, sugar and some yeasts. Taste starts sweet. Full body. Ends slightly bitter. Enjoyable.
Amber colour with way too much foam which stays for a long time. Aroma is sugary, some spices, malts. Taste is quite sweet with a malty touch. Slightly bitter and dry at the end.
Light golden colour with a normal head. Smell: orange zest, sugar, and wheat.Taste: orange, citrus, bitterness, gentle bitterness and dryness at the end. Not a typical white beer, but I like it.

Brown reddish colour. Smell: sourness, sugar, dried plums. Taste: malts, sweetness, bitterness, alcohol and a dry ending. Not what you would expect, knowing the smell and the colour of the beer. Not bad at all.
Blond beer with a lot of foam. Smells a little bit fruity. Taste: hoppy, fruity, orange zest. A nice bitter finish with some dryness. I really like this one!

Golden blond colour with a big head. Aroma: lychee, lychee and lychee and citrus. Very aromatic hops. Taste: grass, citrus, bitterness. The sorachi ace hops are omnipresent. Not bad at all. However, I liked the Duvel Tripel Hop Citra (2012) more.

Light golden colour with a nice head. Aroma: citrus, wheat, herbs. Taste: citrus, some sweetness and a gentle bitter ending.
Good alternative for a pilser. Very easy to drink.
Dark brown colour. Aroma is yeasty and floral. Taste is complex: fruity, yeasty, sugary, chocolate, cookies. Finishes with a subtle bitterness. A Classic!
Dark brown color with a big head. Smells like bread and brown sugar. Taste is fruity, sweet and malty with a very soft bitterness at the end. Not sticky and even a little bit dry. Nice!

Orange/hazy colour with a foamy head. Aroma is yeasty and sugary. Some caramel and bread odors are noticable. Taste: sweetness, caramel (malts?), orange zest, fruitiness. Ends with a very soft bitterness and quite dry.

Golden colour with a big head. Special aroma for a tripel. Some smokiness is noticable. Taste is also quite unusual for a tripel. Relatively sweet, gentle malt taste, alcohol and almost no bitterness. A disappointment for people who expect a bitter beer. However, I think its an original Belgian tripel.
Pours a golden cloudy beer with a nice and firm head. Aroma is yeast and orange. Full body and a warm alcohol feeling. A nice long bitterness and some dryness at the end. Well balanced!

Dark red beer with a small head. Aroma of sweet cherries, marzipan and little bit of sourness.
Taste is similar: sweet cherries, candy, and marzipan. After the sweetness comes in the sourness, which evolves in a new flow of sweetness.
Too sweet and sticky in my opinion.

Dark golden colour, somewhat hazy, with a firm head. Aroma from fruity hops (citrus) and yeast. Taste is hoppy. Hints of banana. A gentle sweetness which disappears for a nice bitterness. Alcoholic (not overwhelming) and dry finish. Recommended.

Pours a dark brown beer with a nice head. Aroma is fruity (cherry) and sugary. Taste is fruity, chocolate and a touch of coffee .A very gentle bitter taste at the end, almost unnoticable. The alcohol gives a warm and pleasing sensation. Very smooth and tasteful!

Copper colour and a nice head. Aroma is sweet (caramel) and some hops. Taste is sweet, fruity and a very gentle bitterness.
Not what you would expect from an IPA. Too little bitterness. Misses some complexity.

Pale yellow colour. Aroma is herby, malty and some sweetness. Taste is a little malty, some sweetness and a gentle bitterness at the end. 
Well balanced. An easy-drinking pilsener, as one expects from a pilsener.

Cloudy golden yellow colour. Aroma is citrus,vanilla, honey and yeast. Taste is orange and honey with a bitter aftertase which is not overwhelming. 
Well balanced and pleasing beer.
Pale golden colour with a big head. Very aromatic hops (citrus) and some spices. Taste is fruity, floral, hoppy and bitter. Nice beer!
Cloudy golden beer. Aroma is sweet, sour, yeast and bread. Taste is similar. Sugary, fruity (banana and exotic fruit) and some bitterness. Rich beer with a slightly dry end. Not bad at all.
Golden colour with a normal head. Malty aroma. Taste is very malty with a light sweetness. Some hoppy bitterness at the end. Well balanced. Very refreshing pilsener.
Golden or hazy colour. Fruity aroma. Taste is fruity at first (citrus, grapefruit), with some spicy elements. Bitter afteraste. Dry at the end. Refreshing and still tasteful. Well done!

azy colour. Almost no head. Aroma is very sour, almost lik a gueuze. Taste is sour, citrus and fruitiness. It has some similarities with wine, probably because of the aging on oak barrels. Very complex taste, very original.
